source.name: Public Health Statistics- Gonorrhea cases for females aged 15 - 44 in Chicago, by year, 2000 -  2011
source.description: The annual number of newly reported, laboratory-confirmed cases of gonorrhea (Neisseria gonorrhoeae) among females aged 15-44 years and annual gonorrhea incidence rate (cases per 100,000 females aged 15-44 years) with corresponding 95% confidence intervals by Chicago community area, for years 2000 – 2011.  See full description at https://data.cityofchicago.org/api/assets/49D71A15-7807-4F5B-8347-94407075137C
